</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"There was an antipathy towards green until well into the 15th century"  Terence Wise, Richard Hook, William Walker Medieval heraldry, vol. 99 of the  Men-at-arms series, <a href="/wiki/Osprey_Publishing" title="Osprey Publishing">Osprey Publishing</a>, 1980, <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-85045-348-5" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-85045-348-5">978-0-85045-348-5</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=fCrjUuziN2cC&amp;q=green&amp;pg=PA11">p. 11</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFDudziński" class="citation interview cs1">Dudziński, Paweł. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://sigillumauthenticum.pl/heraldyka-dudzinski/">"Rozmowy o heraldyce #1: Paweł Dudziński"</a> (Interview). Interviewed by Artur Wójcik. Sigillum Authenticum.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Rozmowy+o+heraldyce+%231%3A+Pawe%C5%82+Dudzi%C5%84ski&amp;rft.pub=Sigillum+Authenticum&amp;rft.aulast=Dudzi%C5%84ski&amp;rft.aufirst=Pawe%C5%82&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fsigillumauthenticum.pl%2Fheraldyka-dudzinski%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AVert+%28heraldry%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">the double cross was used from the 12th century, but the "hill" was added by <a href="/wiki/Louis_I_of_Hungary" title="Louis I of Hungary">Louis I of Hungary</a> (r. 1342-1382), later expanded to "three hills" ("on a mount vert a crown Or, issuant therefrom a double cross argent").</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">ed. Appuhn (1989), <a href="/wiki/File:Siebmacher224.jpg" title="File:Siebmacher224.jpg">p. 224</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Oxford-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Oxford_7-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Oxford_7-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFWoodcockRobinson1988" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Thomas_Woodcock_(officer_of_arms)" title="Thomas Woodcock (officer of arms)">Woodcock, Thomas</a>; <a href="/wiki/John_Martin_Robinson" title="John Martin Robinson">Robinson, John Martin</a> (1988). <i>The Oxford Guide to Heraldry</i>. Oxford: <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. pp.&#160;53–54. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-19-211658-4" title="Special:BookSources/0-19-211658-4"><bdi>0-19-211658-4</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Oxford+Guide+to+Heraldry&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pages=53-54&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.isbn=0-19-211658-4&amp;rft.aulast=Woodcock&amp;rft.aufirst=Thomas&amp;rft.au=Robinson%2C+John+Martin&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AVert+%28heraldry%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Elvin-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Elvin_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Elvin_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFElvin1889" class="citation book cs1">Elvin, Charles Norton (1889). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/cu31924029796426"><i>A Dictionary of Heraldry</i></a>. London: Kent. p.&#160;129.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Dictionary+of+Heraldry&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=129&amp;rft.pub=Kent&amp;rft.date=1889&amp;rft.aulast=Elvin&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles+Norton&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fcu31924029796426&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AVert+%28heraldry%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
